   Impulsesoft and Broadcom Partner To Deliver Comprehensive Bluetooth Solu=
tion for PC OEMs   MONTE CARLO, Monaco, Jun 7, 2001 /PRNewswire via COMTEX/=
 -- Impulsesoft today announced a Bluetooth software partnership with Broad=
com Corporation (Nasdaq: BRCM), supplying a comprehensive hardware and soft=
ware Bluetooth solution for PC original equipment manufacturers (OEMs). Com=
bining Impulsesoft's BluePC(TM) software stack with Broadcom's all-CMOS Blu=
tonium(TM) silicon transceivers, the companies provide a high-performance e=
nd-to-end Bluetooth solution for manufacturers of Windows(R)-compatible des=
ktop and laptop computers. This collaboration between Impulsesoft and Broad=
com will result in a quicker time to market for PC manufactures and their p=
roducts with embedded Bluetooth functionality.   Impulsesoft's BluePC proto=
col stack architecture results in a minimal software footprint and a flexib=
le driver implementation, provides OEMs with the ability to quickly customi=
ze the software for use with their specific implementation. The software st=
ack is Bluetooth version 1.1 certified, significantly easing Bluetooth qual=
ification complexity for the company's PC OEM customers. Broadcom's Blutoni=
um chip family provides strong radio performance, low power consumption, an=
d a choice of version 1.1 qualified baseband chips to accommodate a variety=
 of implementations in embedded PC applications.   "Impulsesoft's single-th=
readed software architecture compliments Broadcom's Bluetooth chipsets by p=
roviding an end-to-end solution with minimal impact on OEMs' designs," said=
 Scott Bibaud, Director of Bluetooth Marketing for Broadcom. "By partnering=
 with Impulsesoft, Broadcom is delivering on its commitment to provide comp=
lete solutions for its customers."   Broadcom's Blutonium chipsets consist =
of multiple version 1.1-compliant radios and basebands, all featuring low p=
ower and developed and manufactured in pure digital CMOS. The BCM2001 and B=
CM2002X are high-performance radios, with the BCM2002X providing a fraction=
al-N interface optimized for use in mobile phones. The BCM2019 and BCM2039 =
are stand-alone baseband chips, featuring host-based and HCI-compliant arch=
itectures, respectively.   "By supporting Broadcom's broad line of chipsets=
 with our flexible stack driver solution, Impulsesoft enables PC manufactur=
ers to implement embedded Bluetooth as they see fit," said K. Srikrishna, C=
hief Executive Officer of Impulsesoft. "And with Windows compliance for the=
 software and Bluetooth qualification for the hardware already achieved, th=
e combined solution expedites time to market for their products."   Impulse=
soft's BluePC   Impulsesoft's BluePC(TM) is a high-performance, versatile B=
luetooth stack driver solution optimized for the Windows operating system o=
n PCs. It operates as a Microsoft Windows Driver Model (WDM) driver that al=
lows for network access and serial port emulation for the applications over=
 the Bluetooth wireless medium. BluePC is the world's first WDM-USB driver =
to be logo-certified. BluePC provides Bluetooth 1.1 support on the Windows9=
8SE, WindowsMe and Windows2000 platforms. Software drivers interact with th=
e lower Bluetooth stack over a number of interfaces including USB, UART and=
 PC Card interfaces.   About Impulsesoft   Impulsesoft Private Limited is a=
 short range wireless solutions company, incorporated in Bangalore, India. =
Impulsesoft is a supplier of Bluetooth software and hardware components for=
 the computing and embedded systems markets. Impulsesoft's products and sys=
tem integration services enable OEMs to bring application specific Bluetoot=
h solutions to market. Impulsesoft, with distributors and VARs worldwide, i=
s an early adopter and Associate Member of the Bluetooth Special Interest G=
roup. Additional information about Impulsesoft is available at http://www.i=
mpulsesoft.com .   Broadcom and Blutonium and the pulse logo are registered=
 trademarks of Broadcom Corporation.   Contact:  Aji Anirudhan of Impulseso=
ft Private Limited, +91-80-658-4160,                or aji@impulsesoft.com =
